author: BBC News
title: Donald Trump rejects CIA Russia hacking report
description: Donald Trump says a CIA report that Russian hackers tried to help him win the election is "ridiculous" and politically-driven.

author: BBC Sport
title: Dario Gradi: Crewe Alexandra director suspended pending FA investigation
description: Crewe director Dario Gradi is suspended pending an FA investigation into claims he "smoothed over" a complaint of sexual assault in the 1970s.

author: BBC News
title: Cairo bombing: Cairo Coptic Christian complex hit
description: A bomb explosion in the Coptic Christian cathedral complex in Egypt's capital kills at least 25.

author: David E. Sanger and Scott Shane
title: Russian Hackers Acted to Aid Trump in Election, U.S. Says
description: Officials have “high confidence” in their conclusion partly because of another finding: Russia hacked Republican Party computers but did not release the information.

author: David E. Sanger
title: Trump, Mocking Claim That Russia Hacked Election, at Odds with G.O.P.
description: Mr. Trump’s team lashed out at intelligence agencies after The Washington Post reported that the C.I.A. believed that Russia had intervened to undercut Hillary Clinton.

author: Nicholas Fandos
title: Donald Trump Ties C.I.A. Reports on Russian Meddling to Democrats’ Shame
description: The president-elect said that he did not believe assessments that Russia had intervened to help him, widening a breach with intelligence agencies.

author: David E. Sanger, Maggie Haberman and Clifford Krauss
title: Rex Tillerson, Exxon Chief, Is Expected to Be Pick for Secretary of State
description: Mr. Tillerson’s extensive deal-making around the world has engendered close ties with a number of world leaders, including President Vladimir V. Putin of Russia.

author: Peter Dominiczak
title: Britain facing energy crisis that could see families pay extra to keep the lights on, Ofgem executive says
description: Britain's increasing reliance on "intermittent" renewable energy means that the country is facing an unprecedented supply crisis, a senior Ofgem executive has warned.

author: Telegraph Reporters
title: Theresa May refuses to shut shops on Boxing Day despite 140,000 petition signatures
description: Theresa May has refused calls to force all shops to close on Boxing Day, saying it is not the Government’s job to tell businesses how they should run their shows.

author: Peter Dominiczak
title: Jeremy Corbyn has 12 months to turn the Labour Party around, according to his closest allies
description: Jeremy Corbyn has 12 months to turn around the Labour’s Party’s dire poll ratings, two of his closest allies have said.

author: Chris Bascombe","Dan Zeqiri
title: Liverpool 2 West Ham 2: Divock Origi salvages point for hosts after Loris Karius blunder further dents title challenge
description: It is no wonder Jürgen Klopp spends so much time in the technical area.

author: John D. McKinnon, Eric Morath and Kristina Peterson
title: Trump Dismisses Claims of Russian Interference in Election
description: President-elect Donald Trump sought to cast doubt on reports that Russia intervened in the 2016 election to boost his chances of winning, saying the reports could be an effort to undercut his presidency.

author: John D. McKinnon and Eric Morath
title: Donald Trump Says Exxon’s Rex Tillerson Would Be ‘World-Class Player’ as Secretary of State
description: President-elect Donald Trump defended Exxon Mobil chief Rex Tillerson—expected to be Mr. Trump’s choice as secretary of state—as a “world-class player” who knows international leaders well.
